sections.title: How the population has changed in Dudley
sections.label: Select another local authority

sections.content: In 2020, Dudley was the fifth largest local authority in the West Midlands, with a total population of 322,363. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Largest local authorities in the West Midlands, 2002-2020
Population density in Dudley
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in Dudley was 3,291 people per square kilometre, which was more than the West Midlands (459), and more than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Densest local authorities in the West Midlands, 2020
Median age in Dudley
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in Dudley was 42 years, which was older than the West Midlands (40 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
